    • Method Detail

      • init

        public static boolean init()
        Method to make the connection to the Northwind Database
        Returns:
        Returns true on successful connection to the database False if the connection failed

      • addCustomer

        public static void addCustomer()
        Adds a customer tuple to the customers table, CustomerID is the primary key and cannot already exist in the table. CustomerID is the only required attribute.

      • addOrder

        public static void addOrder()
        Adds an order to the ORDER and ORDER_DETAILS table. Required values: CustomerID, EmployeeID, OrderDate, ShipVia, ProductID

      • deleteOrder

        public static void deleteOrder()
        Removes the Order specified by the user. This also removes the products from the Order_details table and updates the UnitsOnOrder from the products table with the removed products quantity Required values: OrderID

      • shipOrder

        public static void shipOrder()
        Receives the input from the user for the OrderID and sets the ShippedDate to the current time. Ship Order: Fill in the Orders table with shipping info, ShippedDate, ShipVia, Freight, and check ShipName,ShipAddress, etc to make sure they are not NULL.

      • printOrderDetails

        public static void printOrderDetails()
        Print all the orders with a NULL "ShippedDate"

      • restockParts

        public static void restockParts()
        The user enters the ProductID. If this exists in the products table, then the user is prompted to enter the number of products to add. The number of UnitsOnOrder is subtracted from before the UnitsInStock are added. If the ProductID does not exists, the user is prompted to enter the needed info to add the product to the products table.

      • checkKey

        public static boolean checkKey(java.lang.String table,
                               java.lang.String attribute,
                               java.lang.String value)
        This method takes in the table, attribute and checks if that value is in in the table. This is used to verify foreign keys.
        Parameters:
        table - The table to search for the attribute in
        attribute - The attribute of the table to check
        value - The value to check for
        Returns:
        1 for found, 0 for not found

      • verifyForeignKey

        public static java.lang.String verifyForeignKey(java.lang.String table,
                                                java.lang.String currentAttribute,
                                                java.lang.String foreignAttribute,
                                                int returnType)
        Verifies that a foreign key constraint is met before returning the value
        Parameters:
        table - The other table to check for the foreign key
        currentAttribute - The attribute we are trying to enter into the database
        foreignAttribute - The attribute to check for
        returnType - - 0 for String, 1 for Integer, 2 for Double
        Returns:
        String - the value entered by the user that passes the foreign key constraint

        Parameters:

        charLimit - The limit of the string
        Returns:

      • increaseOnOrder

        public static int increaseOnOrder(java.lang.String table,
                                  java.lang.String updateAttribute,
                                  java.lang.String keyAttribute,
                                  java.lang.String key,
                                  int increment)
        Updates the attribute in updateAttribute field with the increment integer. The keyAttribute, key is used to select the tuple
        Parameters:
        table - The table to update in
        updateAttribute - The attribute / field to update
        keyAttribute - The Primary Key field for the table
        key - The Primary key we are searching for to distinguish the tuple
        increment - The amount to increment the field
        Returns:
        Returns 1 on failure and 0 on success

      • getOrderID

        public static int getOrderID()
        Receives the OrderID from the user. Doesn't allow negative numbers. Also checks that the OrderID exists in the orders table and that the ShippedDate value is null (meaning the order hasn't shipped).
        Returns:
        Integer - the value of the OrderID to mark as shipped

      • nullShippedDate

        Parameters:
        OrderID - The OrderID to check for
        Returns:
        True if the ShippedDate is null, false otherwise
